COMMAND: NovaScript Loops

HOW TO USE:
while [condition] { ... }
for <var> in <start> to <end> { ... }

EXAMPLE:
set i = 1
while [i <= 5] {
  print i
  set i = i + 1
}

for i in 1 to 3 {
  print i
}

DESCRIPTION:
NovaScript supports both `while` and `for` constructs. `while` evaluates a
boolean expression and executes its body while true. `for` uses a start
and end integer; it iterates inclusive of the end value.

LANGUAGE:
NovaScript

NOTES:
- The runtime enforces a `MAX_ITERATIONS` count to protect from infinite
  loops.
- Use `set var = expr` within the loop to modify counter variables.

WARNINGS:
- Infinite loops are detected and throw an error if the iteration limit
  is exceeded.
